public static int hammingWeight(int n) {
	int ones = 0;
    	while(n!=0) {
    		ones = ones + (n & 1);
    		n = n>>>1;
    	}
    	return ones;
}

Note:
The algorithm counts the number of set bits in an integer. It checks the last bit using n & 1 and adds it to the count.
Then it right shifts the number using >>> 1 to process the next bit until the number becomes zero.

5 = 101
Steps:
n (binary)	n & 1	ones	n >>> 1
101	           1	 1	    10
10	           0	  1	     1
1	             1	  2	     0
Final result:
ones = 2 
